channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Derrick Rose, a No. 1 overall pick in 2008 and the 2011 NBA MVP, announces retirement
item.description: Derrick Rose, the No. 1 overall pick in the 2008 NBA draft by the Chicago Bulls and the league’s MVP in 2011, announced his retirement on Thursday

item.title: Lawmakers push for accountability after 10th death linked to Boar’s Head listeria outbreak
Disney+ to hike prices and crack down on password sharing
item.description: Disney follows in the footsteps of Netflix in looking to convert Disney+ password-borrowers into paying customers.

item.title: Hurricane Helene live updates: Track path as Florida braces for landfall
item.description: Helene -- which strengthened to a Category 1 hurricane on Wednesday morning -- is taking aim at Florida, where it's forecast to make landfall along the Big Bend area.

item.title: What Is the Social Security ‘Break-Even’ Point? How Long You Need To Live To Make Waiting Worth It
Rudy Giuliani disbarred in D.C., months after disbarment in New York
item.description: Former New York City Mayor Rudy Giuliani has been disbarred from practicing law in the nation's capital, a D.C. appeals court ruled.

item.title: US economy grew at a solid 3% rate last quarter, government says in final estimate
item.description: The American economy expanded at a healthy 3% annual pace from April through June, boosted by strong consumer spending and business investment, the government said, leaving its previous estimate unchanged

item.title: Here are the 4 levels of wealth for American retirees — how do you compare?
Israel's military hints at Lebanon ground operations against Hezbollah
item.description: Israel may be preparing for a ground operation inside of Lebanon against the Hezbollah militant group as conflict in the Middle East grows. CBS News' Chris Livesay reports.

item.title: Americans can again order 4 free at-home COVID tests from federal government
item.description: Starting Thursday, Americans can order four free at-home COVID tests from the federal government ahead of respiratory virus season.

item.title: Effort to force vote on Social Security bill stirs unrest in House GOP
Helene gets stronger as it approaches Florida
item.description: Hurricane Helene is getting stronger as it approaches Florida, potentially making landfall Thursday evening or early Friday morning. Helene may bring catastrophic winds and heavy rain to many parts of Florida and Georgia. CBS News meteorologist David Yeomans has more.

item.title: The number of Americans filing for jobless aid falls to lowest level in 4 months
item.description: The number of Americans applying for unemployment benefits last week fell to the lowest level in four months

item.title: 2 Super Cybersecurity Stocks to Buy Hand Over Fist as 2025 Approaches
What travelers can expect as Hurricane Helene nears Florida
item.description: As Hurricane Helene aims for Florida, the Tampa Airport has already suspended operations and is closed to the public. Other Florida airports could be impacted, along with Atlanta's airport and as far north as Charlotte, North Carolina.
